---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
    title="About Calculemus"
    description="The student-run AI team at Leiden University (LIACS)."
    pubDate={new Date('May 08 2026')}
>
    <img src="/us.jpg" alt="The Calculemus team" />

    <p>
        <strong>"Calculemus"</strong> means <em>Let us calculate</em>. It's a phrase from Leibniz, who wanted to solve problems purely through computation. We're a team of computer science and AI students of <strong>Leiden University (LIACS)</strong> solving challenges of the current (scientific) community.
    </p>

    <h4>What we do</h4>
    <p>
        We focus on the mechanics of artificial intelligence, by participating all kinds of AI-related challenges. We like to puzzle and be creative. Our team consists of AI engineers, coordinators and team managers.
    </p>

    <h4>The Community</h4>
    <p>
        Studying AI is easier (and a lot more fun) when you aren't doing it alone. Calculemus acts as a place for students who want to build, debug, or research together. We run a few main events throughout the year:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Tech Talks:</strong> Technical deep dives by (LIACS) researchers and industry.</li>
        <li><strong>Hackathons:</strong> Short (and highly energized) sprints to build working models from scratch.</li>
        <li><strong>Game Nights:</strong> Low-key evenings where we bring laptops, grab pizza, and try to beat our self-made agents.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>On top of that, we host interviews with current leaders and pioneers in the AI landscape. Feel free to reach out if you're having an interesting research-topic.</p>

    <h4>Join us</h4>
    <p>
        Whether you're a master's student training models for your thesis or a first-year who just wrote their first PyTorch training loop, you're welcome here. Check out our <a href="/events">Events</a> page to see when we're meeting next.
    </p>
</Layout>